âš¡ 1. UPS

The UPS represents the actual power backup equipment feeding downstream components.

For each UPS, provide:

Make & Model (e.g., Vertiv 600KVA EXL-S1)

KVA Rating, KW Rating, and Voltage (V) values

Location (Site â†’ Room / Ceiling name)

Status (Planned / Installed)



This data defines where the UPS unit is physically located and what load it supports.


---

ğŸ”‹ 2. UPS Bank

For every UPS, there should be one corresponding UPS Bank.

The UPS Bank acts as the distribution point that receives power from the UPS.

The UPS Bank Rating (Amps) is derived from the UPSâ€™s KW or KVA rating.

The UPS Bank also serves as the housing for Load Devices that connect the power flow between the UPS and PDU.



