ğŸ”Œ 3. Load Devices

Load Devices represent the actual electrical connection path between the UPS, UPS Bank, and PDUs.
There are two main types of Load Devices in this context:

A. Load Device â€“ UPS â†’ UPS Bank

Purpose: Carries power from the UPS to its corresponding UPS Bank.

Line Side: Extension

Load Side: Bus

Power Fed From: The UPS itself.

Source: UPS Name : UPS Output

Device Name Convention: UPS Name + " Breaker" (e.g., UPS A1 Breaker).

Model: Load Device â€“ 3 Pole.

Example Entry:

Power Fed From â†’ UPS A1 : UPS Output

Line Side â†’ Extension

Load Side â†’ Bus A

Location â†’ STLEMITX > UPS Room 303

Rating â†’ 600 Amps



B. Load Device â€“ UPS Bank â†’ PDU

Purpose: Carries power from the UPS Bank to the Floor PDU.

Line Side: Bus

Load Side: Extension

Power Fed From: The UPS Bank output.

Source: UPS Bank Name : Output

Device Name Convention: PDU Name + " Breaker" (e.g., PDU B12 Breaker).

Model: Load Device â€“ 3 Pole.

